column2: SELECT JULIANDAY(event_log.timestamp) - JULIANDAY(MIN(event_log.timestamp)) AS time_elapsed FROM event_log WHERE event_log.idcase IN ( SELECT idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity LIKE '%fim da viagem%' OR activity LIKE '%declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário%' OR activity LIKE '%pagamento efetuado%' );
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Fim da viagem', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Pagamento efetuado' from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'Fim da viagem' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário'  left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Pagamento efetuado'

column2: SELECT JULIANDAY(el2.timestamp) - JULIANDAY(el1.timestamp) AS tempo_decorrido FROM event_log AS el1 JOIN event_log AS el2 ON el1.idcase = el2.idcase WHERE el1.activity IN ('início da viagem', 'declaração enviada pelo funcionário') AND el2.activity IN ('fim da viagem', 'declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário', 'pagamento efetuado');

column2: SELECT event_log.idcase, event_log.activity, ( event_log.timestamp - ( SELECT MIN(timestamp) FROM event_log WHERE idcase = event_log.idcase ) ) AS time_since_first_event FROM event_log WHERE event_log.activity IN ('fim da viagem', 'declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário', 'pagamento efetuado') ORDER BY event_log.idcase, time_since_first_event DESC;
column3: select p.idcase, strftime('%s', p.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Fim da viagem', strftime('%s', x.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário', strftime('%s', y.timestamp) - strftime('%s', e.start_time) as 'Pagamento efetuado', f.activity from event_log p inner join (select MIN(timestamp) as start_time, idcase FROM event_log GROUP by idcase) e on e.idcase = p.idcase and p.activity = 'Fim da viagem' left join event_log x on x.idcase=e.idcase and x.activity = 'Declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário' left join event_log y on y.idcase=e.idcase and y.activity = 'Pagamento efetuado' inner join (select MAX(timestamp) as end_time, activity, idcase FROM event_log WHERE activity='Fim da viagem' or activity= 'Declaração rejeitada pelo funcionário' or activity='Pagamento efetuado' GROUP by idcase) f on f.idcase=e.idcase

column2: SELECT AVG(timestamp - timestamp) FROM event_log GROUP BY activity;
column3: WITH RankedEvents AS (SELECT id, activity, timestamp, LEAD(timestamp) OVER (PARTITION BY idcase ORDER BY timestamp) AS next_timestamp, idcase FROM event_log), DurationEvents AS (SELECT activity, (strftime('%s', next_timestamp) - strftime('%s', timestamp)) as duration FROM RankedEvents WHERE next_timestamp IS NOT NULL) SELECT activity, AVG(duration) AS average_duration FROM DurationEvents GROUP BY activity
